          "role": "assistant",
          "seq": 2,
          "text": "## Starting
The session begins in \`starting\`, which is the pre-connection phase. In the state machine, nothing interactive is allowed here yet: the runtime is still establishing the ACP session, and the machine is waiting for either a \`SessionReady\` event from \`newSession\` or a \`ReplayStarted\` event if it is reconstructing a prior session.

## Replaying
A \`ReplayStarted\` event moves the machine from \`starting\` to \`replaying\`. This phase is used when an existing session is being loaded back in, so the machine creates a replay turn and collects historical turn data until \`ReplayEnded\` arrives. When replay finishes, the replay turn is committed and the machine transitions to \`ready\`.

## Ready
\`ready\` is the idle, interactive phase. The user can submit a prompt here, which the machine validates through \`decide(Prompt, ...)\` and then converts into a \`PromptStarted\` event. The first thing \`PromptStarted\` does is open a live turn and record the synthesized user message as the first update in that turn.

## Working
\`working\` means a live turn is in progress. Incoming \`Updated\` events are folded into the active turn, each one getting a sequence number and being appended to the turn’s update list. The machine stays in \`working\` until the runtime signals \`TurnEnded\`, which commits the turn, records its final \`stopReason\` when present, and returns the session to \`ready\`.

## Cancelling
\`cancelling\` is a transient phase entered when the user cancels an in-flight turn. The machine first drains any pending permission requests as cancelled, then keeps the active turn in place while the runtime finishes shutting down the agent-side work. When \`TurnEnded\` eventually arrives, the turn is committed and the machine returns to \`ready\`.

## Closed
\`closed\` is the terminal phase. It is entered when the underlying process exits or the connection is closed, via \`ProcessClosed\`. If a turn is still active at that moment, the machine commits it as an error turn, clears pending permissions, and records the exit code on the phase.

## Example Event Flow
\`\`\`text
starting
  -> ReplayStarted
replaying
  -> ReplayEnded
ready
  -> PromptStarted
working
  -> Updated
working
  -> Updated
working
  -> TurnEnded(stopReason = "end_turn")
ready
  -> ProcessClosed(exitCode = 0)
closed
\`\`\`

## How The Pieces Fit
\`session-machine.ts\` owns the lifecycle rules, validation, and state folding. \`acp-session-runtime.ts\` sits above it, translating ACP client activity into domain events like \`SessionReady\`, \`PromptStarted\`, \`Updated\`, \`TurnEnded\`, and \`ProcessClosed\`, so the machine stays pure and deterministic.",
        },
      ],
